    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "That's a good start for the students to get the gist of it. I'm a bit worried, though, that some students might get confused if they hear people arguing that this doctrine is actually a 'judicial invention' or that it's not a real part of the Constitution. How should I address those critics who say that 'substantive due process' is just an excuse for judges to make up rights that aren't actually written in the text?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
