      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "You can explain that critics argue the Supreme Court creates Fifth and Fourteenth Amendment vagueness by broadly defining rights, while defenders assert it reflects historical customs and will to legal evolution. To help students see both sides, compare specific landmark cases where the Court has protected rights that preceded textbook definitions of \"substantive\" vs \"procedural\" due process. Emphasize that this debate itself is a core part of American constitutional history and invites students to evaluate how they would balance judicial oversight with legislative power.",
