    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "I like the idea of showing both sides. However, when I talk to these critics, they don't just say it's a \"debate\"—they argue it's actually a dangerous way for unelected judges to bypass the democratic process and impose their own progressive values on the country. In your view, is there a legitimate legal basis for these critics, or is their argument just a way to try and roll back established civil rights?",
