      "content": "There is a legitimate legal weight to these critics' arguments regarding the \"counter-majoritarian difficulty,\" as the Supreme Court does indeed interpret the Constitution rather than reflecting the current majority's political will. While proponents argue this is necessary to protect fundamental rights against democratic overreach or \"tyranny of the majority,\" opponents contend it allows unelected judges to impose controversial social values. Ultimately, the tension you face reflects the ongoing American struggle to define the proper relationship between judicial interpretation and the democratic electorate.",
